    "description": "Kernel Density Estimation (KDE): Create a continuous probability density function or cumulative distribution function from discrete samples. The basic idea is to smooth the data using a kernel function. to help draw inferences about a population from a sample. The degree of smoothing is controlled by the scaling parameter h which is called the bandwidth. Smaller values emphasize local features while larger values give smoother results. The kernel determines the relative weights of the sample ...",
